  <prompt>
    Handlebars.NET has no native `lambda`. The DAILY-BRIEFING-NARRATE source uses
    `(lambda c (map c.items 'regardingName'))` inside the ValidateEntityNames allowList expression
    — needed because `start.categories[]` is an array of objects each containing an `items[]`
    sub-array (categories → items → regardingName). Rather than build a true lambda helper
    (complex), register a single `{{flatMap COLL 'nested.path'}}` helper that handles
    "for each item in COLL, traverse 'nested.path' on it, return flat array". Then rewrite the
    source playbook JSON's allowList expression using `flatMap`. Net: one helper, one source edit,
    no lambda complexity in the engine.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    SPAARKE platform developer. Same expertise as 112 (Handlebars.NET) + JPS authoring
    familiarity. Goal: simplest engine + cleanest source — pick the form that's easier to read.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `TemplateEngine.cs` registers a `flatMap` helper. `daily-briefing-narrate.json` source has its
    ValidateEntityNames allowList expression rewritten using `flatMap` (no `lambda`). xUnit tests
    for the helper. Update task 115 to PATCH the deployed `sprk_playbooknode` row with the rewritten
    expression (deferred — 115 handles deployed-data restoration).
  </prompt>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="template-engine">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/TemplateEngine.cs</file>
    <file purpose="template-engine-tests">tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/TemplateEngineTests.cs</file>
    <file purpose="source-playbook">projects/spaarke-daily-update-service/notes/playbooks/daily-briefing-narrate.json</file>
    <file purpose="source-action">projects/spaarke-daily-update-service/notes/playbooks/actions/brief-validate-entity-names.action.json</file>
    <file purpose="design-from-110">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/notes/spikes/wave11-orchestrator-resolution-design.md</file>
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-010">DI Minimalism — helper added to existing TemplateEngine; no new abstraction.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029">BFF Publish Hygiene — no new packages.</constraint>
    <constraint source="CLAUDE.md §10">BFF Hygiene checklist applies.</constraint>
    <constraint source="CLAUDE.md §11">Helper is extension of existing TemplateEngine; source JSON edit is modification. No new component justification required.</constraint>
    <constraint source="readability">After rewrite, the source allowList expression MUST be readable in &lt; 5 lines (current lambda version spans 1 multi-line expression).</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <topic>ai/template-engine-helpers</topic>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md</file>
      <file>.claude/constraints/testing.md</file>
      <file>docs/adr/ADR-010-di-minimalism.md</file>
      <file>docs/adr/ADR-029-bff-publish-hygiene.md</file>
