      <file>docs/guides/JPS-AUTHORING-GUIDE.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/notes/spikes/wave11-orchestrator-resolution-design.md</file>
    </files>
    <patterns>
      <pattern name="flatMap semantic" location="JavaScript Array.prototype.flatMap">
        Equivalent of `arr.flatMap(item =&gt; lookup(item, 'nested.path'))`. C# equivalent: `coll.SelectMany(item =&gt; ResolveDottedPath(item, fieldPath).AsEnumerable())`.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="dotted-path resolution" location="TemplateEngine.ConvertJsonElement output shape">
        Items in ConvertJsonElement output are Dictionary&lt;string, object?&gt; (case-insensitive). Walk dotted path by splitting on '.' and indexing each level. Final value may be IEnumerable (array case) or scalar.
      </pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>
      Current source `ValidateEntityNames.inputBinding.allowList` uses:
      `{{distinct (concat (map start.priorityItems 'regardingName') ... (flatten (map start.categories (lambda c (map c.items 'regardingName')))) ...)}}`
      The `(lambda c (map c.items 'regardingName'))` is needed because categories is array-of-objects each with items[]. Adding a true Handlebars lambda is complex (block helper + subexpression capture); adding a `flatMap` helper sidesteps the issue with one straightforward addition.
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      <dependency task="111" status="must-complete-first">ITemplateEngine wired so the helper is reachable.</dependency>
    </dependencies>
    <related-work>
      <item>Task 112 adds 6 other helpers (json, map, flatten, distinct, concat, join). T113 adds the 7th (flatMap).</item>
      <item>Task 115 PATCHes the deployed sprk_playbooknode row with the rewritten allowList expression.</item>
    </related-work>
  </context>

  <steps>
    <step order="0" name="Rigor Declaration">
      Output: 🔒 RIGOR LEVEL: FULL · 📋 REASON: bff-api code-impl + edits canonical source JSON · Proceeding with Step 0...
    </step>
    <step order="1" name="Load context + verify 111 complete">
      Confirm 111 ✅. Read design doc from 110. Read existing JoinIds helper for defensive style.
    </step>
    <step order="2" name="Implement flatMap helper">
      Register `_handlebars.RegisterHelper("flatMap", …)`. Signature: `{{flatMap COLL 'nested.path'}}`. Internals: walk COLL items, for each item resolve dotted-path (split + index step-by-step on Dictionary&lt;string,object?&gt;), collect via SelectMany. Returns flat List&lt;object?&gt;. Null guard + UndefinedBindingResult guard per existing style.
    </step>
    <step order="3" name="Write xUnit tests for flatMap">
      Test cases:
      (a) Happy path — array of objects each with array sub-field (categories → items → regardingName);
      (b) Empty outer array → empty result;
      (c) Item missing nested.path → null entries skipped or kept (decision: skip);
      (d) Scalar at intermediate path → empty;
      (e) JsonElement input via ConvertJsonElement;
      (f) Single-level path (no dots) → equivalent to flatten+map.
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Rewrite source playbook allowList expression">
      Edit `projects/spaarke-daily-update-service/notes/playbooks/daily-briefing-narrate.json`. Replace the lambda-based `allowList` expression with flatMap-based form. Example new shape:
      `{{distinct (concat (map start.priorityItems 'regardingName') (map start.priorityItems 'viaMatter.name') (map start.priorityItems 'source.owningUser') (flatMap start.categories 'items.regardingName') (flatMap start.categories 'items.viaMatter.name') (flatMap start.categories 'items.source.owningUser') (flatMap start.channels 'items.regardingName') (flatMap start.channels 'items.viaMatter.name') (flatMap start.channels 'items.source.owningUser'))}}`
      Preserve the `_comment` documenting the FR-3 / FR-14 rationale; add a brief note on the lambda → flatMap rewrite.
    </step>
    <step order="5" name="Verify no remaining lambda in source">
      Grep `projects/spaarke-daily-update-service/notes/playbooks/` for `lambda`. Confirm zero matches after edit.
    </step>
    <step order="6" name="Build + run BFF test suite">
      `dotnet build` + `dotnet test` — confirm zero regressions.
    </step>
    <step order="7" name="Step 9.5 — Quality gates">
      `/code-review` + `/adr-check` on the TemplateEngine + test changes. Address HIGH/CRITICAL.
    </step>
    <step order="8" name="Update TASK-INDEX + current-task.md">
      Mark 113 ✅; advance to next pending (114).
    </step>
    <step order="9" name="Commit">
      Commit message body cites the lambda-to-flatMap decision + reference to design doc.
    </step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool>Read (TemplateEngine + source playbook)</tool>
